President Obama has issued a proclamation for Earth Day, emphasizing the importance of protecting the environment. He highlights America's role as a technological leader and its responsibility to safeguard the planet. The proclamation reflects on the first Earth Day as a catalyst for change and the subsequent progress made in environmental legislation and conservation efforts. The President discusses his Administration's initiatives, such as the America's Great Outdoors program and standards to reduce toxic emissions. He acknowledges the urgent threat of climate change and emphasizes the need for action. The President mentions fuel efficiency standards, investments in clean energy, and engagement with stakeholders at home and abroad. He calls on Congress to pursue a bipartisan, market-based solution to climate change and directs his Cabinet to develop executive actions to reduce pollution and prepare communities for the consequences of climate change. President Obama encourages Americans to participate in programs and activities that protect the environment and contribute to a sustainable future.